HANOI, Nov. 12 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam reported 8,982 new COVID-19 cases on Friday, including 8,976 locally transmitted and six imported, according to its Ministry of Health. Most of the community cases were detected in southern localities, including 1,388 in Ho Chi Minh City, 813 in Dong Nai province, and 661 in An Giang province. The infections brought the total tally to 1,009,879, with 22,930 deaths, said the ministry. Nationwide, as many as 856,211 patients have so far recovered, up 10,263 from Thursday. Nearly 97 million doses of COVID-19 vaccines, including some 33 million second doses, have been administered, according to the ministry. As of Friday, the country has registered a total of 1,004,879 locally transmitted COVID-19 cases since the start of the current wave in late April, the ministry said. Enditem